data.title: Nano-snakemake
data.description: A snakemake pipeline for SV analysis from nanopore genome sequencing
data.name: nano-snakemake

evidence: "A snakemake pipeline for nanopore whole genome sequencing structural variant analysis."

"Conda environment files containing the dependencies can be found in the `envs` directory. These can be automatically installed and managed by providing the `--use-conda` argument to snakemake: `snakemake --use-conda ...`." (indicates users run the pipeline directly)

"The folder "scripts" contains scripts necessary for the pipeline.   The folder "extra_scripts" contains scripts I wrote while playing around with the results, mainly visualizations." (repository- and source-centric distribution, no mention of package registries or binaries)
